    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>[Congressional Record Volume 161, Number 92 (Wednesday, June 10, 2015)]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [<a href='http://www.gpo.gov'>www.gpo.gov</a>]By Mr. McKINLEY:H.R. 2724.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:According to Article I, Section 8, Clause 3 of theConstitution: The Congress shall have power to enact thislegislation to regulate commerce with foreign nations, andamong the several states, and with the Indian tribes.[Page H4137]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
